Pros cons and advices- The Analogues!!
May 2023 • Solo
PROS
* Amazing theatre in every way
* Classic seating arrangement
* Impressive interior concert hall
* Fantastic acoustics which are not painful or too loud
* Beautiful outside structure and appearance, especially when illuminated at night
* Varied and wonderful line-up of acts and performances
* Helpful young staff members
* Coat and bag check storage services apparently free of charge
* Food, dinner and drinks offered too
* Prices are very reasonable compared to other venues and locations

CONS
* Some seats are obstructed view
* Getting to or leaving seats in the circular raised sections could mean passing at the knees of fifteen or more people
* Hallways and staircases are narrow and crowded and obstructed before and after performances

"I VISITED THIS PLACE"...
... because I specifically came from Israel to Amsterdam in order to see two performances of the Analogues at this Koninklijk Carre Theatre. It was great and fantastic show and I loved it so much that I returned again on the next night for another identical performance (see my many photos of them, shown from two sides of the hall)!! I told the person next to me both times that I had traveled all the way from Israel to see the performances- neither was impressed by that.

The building and the concert area is fantastic and classic and I liked it so much. There are apparently non permanent seats on the main floor opposite and in front of the stage. I sat in a low side tier of partially obstructed seats for both shows, but on opposite sides (see again my photos).

The building is very beautiful and special, especially when illuminated and seen from the bridge over the canal (see my "helpful" photos).

There were very many special unique people crowded into the aisles and passageways both before and after the performance.

I'd be happy to return again... for another performance by the Analogues!

ADVICES
* You will certainly enjoy just seeing this illuminated structure at night
* It's a great place for performances

Written July 25, 2023

Glen Hansard OH MY DAYS
Apr 2019 • Friends
Went here last night to watch the second Glen Hansard gig in Amsterdam.

We arrived from central on the Metro which took us to one street away from the venue. The walk along the canal really set the tone for the evening. The front of the venue was awesome and after having our electronic tickets scanned we were given instructions on where to go.

As the warm-up act was performing we were unable to enter the theatre so we went up to the bar. The classy set up with doors to the balcony which allows you to look over the canal whilst enjoying a drink and atmosphere.

Upon entry into the actual theatre, we were told where our seats were and headed towards them. What struck me the most was how beautiful the inside of the venue was. A decent size, with a touch of class but extremely intimate.

Glen had a 9 piece band with him and the show was out o this world He was able to perform without a microphone for two songs and the sound travelled with ease.

- Fantastic venue
- Great friendly and helpful staff
- Amazing Gig
Written May 1, 2019
